CONTEXT Try1 IN ENGLISH

PATTERN Try1
RELATION r[A*B]
CLASSIFY A ISA B
RULE r  |-  (V[A*A]-I[B]) ; r
RULE r  |-  (V[A*B]-I[B]) ; r
RULE r  |-  (V[B*A]-I[B]) ; r
RULE r  |-  (V[B*B]-I[B]) ; r
RULE r  |-         -I[B]  ; r
ENDPATTERN

ENDCONTEXT
{- 
   Purpose: to verify that the complement of I[B] is unambiguous (line 10).
   Result: PASS

   Historical note:
   This file was originally placed in shouldFail because the old Ampersand type checker
   treated the complement operator (-) as producing a type-unbound expression (similar to V).
   In that design, -I[B] with CLASSIFY A ISA B was ambiguous, because several
   universe types were possible: V[A*A]-I[B], V[A*B]-I[B], V[B*A]-I[B], V[B*B]-I[B].

   Design decision (current type checker):
   The current type checker assigns the complement -e the same type as e itself.
   Because I[B] has exactly one signature [B*B], its complement -I[B] unambiguously
   has type [B*B] as well. Within the universe of all declared relations, this is the
   only valid interpretation, so no ambiguity arises. The user is free to use the
   explicit forms on lines 6-9 when a different universe is intended.
-}
